# Tempo Deck — Base Conventions

## EXECUTION PROTOCOL
1. SEARCH FIRST — grep/find similar functionality before implementing anything
2. REUSE FIRST — extend existing components/helpers (reuse BeatCounter / TempoBadge / SessionList)
3. READ BEFORE EDIT — always read a file's current content before modifying
4. NO ASSUMPTIONS — only use facts from read files, user messages, tool results
5. VERIFY — run `npx tsc --noEmit` + `npm run lint` after every change
6. PLAN FIRST — multi-file changes start in Plan mode; execute after the plan holds
7. FEEDBACK LOOP — self-correct on failures before committing; never commit unverified work

## CORE CONVENTIONS
- Language: TypeScript 5 (strict)
- Package manager: npm (package-lock.json)
- Module system: ESM
- Exports: named for components; route entry files (app/page.tsx, app/layout.tsx) also export default
- File naming: kebab-case files, PascalCase components

## COMMANDS
- Dev: `npm run dev`
- Lint: `npm run lint`
- Typecheck: `npx tsc --noEmit`
- Build: `npm run build`
- (no test command — no test runner installed)

## NEVER
- NEVER assume a function or import exists — search first
- NEVER add packages without checking package.json first
- NEVER reference paths that don't exist — no src/, no app/api/, no middleware.ts, no database; `@/` resolves to the project root
- NEVER use "think step by step" with reasoning models — they reason internally
